description: The old Seoul Station, established in 1925, has been the gateway of Seoul's transportation for the past 80 years. After KTX opened in 2004, the old Seoul Station was no longer used as a train station. The abandoned old Seoul Station was not put into use until after the internal restoration project in 2011, the comprehensive cultural space named "Culture Station Seoul 284" met the citizens again. The name of "Culture Station Seoul 284" was designated after an open call in Korea. The name includes the cultural network center, the regionality of Seoul, and historical site No. 284.

address: 39, Gocheok-ro 45-gil, Guro-gu, Seoul Guro-gu Min Sports Center San 9-14, Gocheok-dong, Guro-gu, Seoul
